Certainly! Below is a simple HTML code for a web app that generates a random name for your penis. This includes embedded CSS for styling and JavaScript for functionality, all within a single HTML file.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Penis Name Generator</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            color: #333;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        h1 {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .name {
            font-size: 24px;
            font-weight: bold;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #007bff;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            font-size: 16px;
            background-color: #28a745;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #218838;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Random Penis Name Generator</h1>
    <div class="name" id="penisName">Press the button to generate a name!</div>
    <button onclick="generateName()">Generate Name</button>

    <script>
        const adjectives = [
            "Slick", "Mighty", "Tiny", "Epic", "Magical", "Fearless", "Charming", "Radiant",
            "Dashing", "Wily", "Noble", "Wild", "Majestic", "Bold", "Sneaky", "Gallant"
        ];
        const nouns = [
            "Dragon", "Wand", "Unicorn", "Sword", "Thunder", "Beast", "Hero", "Titan",
            "Monster", "Phoenix", "Legend", "Avenger", "Knight", "Shark", "Fury", "King"
        ];

        function generateName() {
            const randomAdjective = adjectives[Math.floor(Math.random() * adjectives.length)];
            const randomNoun = nouns[Math.floor(Math.random() * nouns.length)];
            document.getElementById("penisName").textContent = `${randomAdjective} ${randomNoun}`;
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How to Use
1. Copy the code above.
2. Paste it into a `.html` file (for example, `penis_name_generator.html`).
3. Open that file in a web browser.

You will see a title, a prompt to generate a name, and a button. Each time you click the "Generate Name" button, a random name composed of an adjective and a noun will be displayed. Enjoy!
